I have an iOS app written in modern Swift. The iOS app allows for the scanning of UPC barcodes and adding the health and data results from an open API call into the database of foods in the app. The entire feature was developed; however, the API migrated from v1 to v2 and in doing so the code broke. I have fixed the code 90%, but I am struggling to get the data that is being called by the new v2 API to populate into the app, so I need help mapping the values into the app for insertion into the app database. I am very close to figuring this out, but I have to move on to other things, so I think someone who is a bit more experienced could find the issue in 1-2 hours or less. 
I have 4 web views in the app and 4 controller codes in SWIFT that need to be converted.&nbsp;&nbsp;
I would also like help setting up a CI/CD workflow for these apps using XCode Cloud or GitHub actions whichever one makes the most sense.<b>Skills</b>:        Firebase Realtime Database,                     Firebase Cloud Firestore,                     Native App Development,                     Push Notifications,                     Firebase,                     Apple Xcode,                     iOS SDK,                     Twilio API,                     WebRTC,                     WebKit,                     Swift,                     iOS Development,                     Smartphone,                     Mobile App Development,                     Objective-C

